                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the central shrine in the ruined Ādivarāha Perumāḷ temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Śadāśivadēva-mahārāya. Ś. 1483: 1562 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date given in this inscription, viz., Śaka 1483, Duṉmati, Makara śu 10, Rōhiṇi, Wednesday, regularly correspond to 1562 A.D. January 14.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the gift of Ālambaṭṭu on the northern bank of Kuḍiāṟu in Perumugaipaṟṟu in Śiṅgaporuda-vaḷanāḍu in Palkuṉṟa-kkōṭṭam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam to god Paḷḷikoṇḍa Perumāḷ for offering and services for the god at the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> on the bank of the tank named after Timmunāyakkar when the god was taken out in procession in the course of the festival of the hunting expedition (<hi rend="italic">pāḍivēṭṭai</hi>), by <hi rend="italic">Amaram</hi> Śiṉṉappa Nā[ya]kkar of Tōḍālam.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
